ommunity, and this opportunity is just one more signifier of that.', 68134, 0), (452171, 'How do you rebel in a family of rebels?', 67437, 0), (452172, 'Family holidays and weekends are really brightly colored memories, full of my mother and father, rather than our nannies and au pairs.', 70347, 0), (452173, 'Around my house, I won''t even speak to my family unless they first address me by my official Berzerker name, Godred Crovan, Victor of Sky-Hill and Ruler of Man and the Isles. And now that I think of it, that''s probably why nobody speaks to me unless it''s time to feed the dogs or take out the garbage.', 69681, 0), (452174, 'While I have felt lonely many times in my life, the oddest feeling of all was after my mother, Lucille, died. My father had already died, but I always had some attachment to our big family while she was alive. It seems strange to say now that I felt so lonely, yet I did.', 31358, 0), (452175, 'My ideal travel companions are my family.', 70689, 0), (452176, 'As straight Americans we have two choices: we can choose to sit back and enjoy our rights as we have them, or we can realize that it is actually not freedom at all when our friends, family, neighbors, and colleagues do not share these basic rights.', 72270, 0), (452177, 'Nature is a machine. The family is a machine. The life cycle is like a machine.', 29403, 0), (452178, 'Coming home to my family afterward makes the work richer, easier and more fun.', 69147, 0), (452179, 'I''ll paddle board, swim in the ocean, roll in the sand, soak up the sun, eat good food, be with friends and family and go fishing with my dad.', 72271, 0), (452180, 'I always loved family holidays, and I had this vision and dream as a little girl of having a big family of my own.', 72272, 0), (452181, 'I don''t believe in revenge. When people are bullies it''s because of a deeper-rooted issue - either their family life is tough or they''re being bullied by someone bigger than they are.', 66708, 0), (452182, 'Every family is dysfunctional, whether you want to admit it or not.', 52537, 0), (452183, 'Insanity runs in my family. It practically gallops.', 1363, 0), (452184, 'I find the family the most mysterious and fascinating institution in the world.', 31044, 0), (452185, 'When I was in China, Mao was Chairman, and parents were terrified to tell their children anything that differed from the party line in case the children repeated it and endangered the whole family.', 17789, 0), (452186, 'My biggest hobby is hanging out with my family and kids.', 3956, 0), (452187, 'Family quarrels are bitter things. They don''t go according to any rules. They''re not like aches or wounds, they''re more like splits in the skin that won''t heal because there''s not enough material.', 97, 0), (452188, 'Whatever else is unsure in this stinking dunghill of a world a mother''s love is not.', 265, 0), (452189, 'Having family responsibilities and concerns just has to make you a more understanding person.', 10500, 0), (452190, 'My family is more important than my party.', 72273, 0), (452191, 'I''ve always put my family first and that''s just the way it is.', 47322, 0), (452192, 'My family was my guide to my reality.', 72274, 0), (452193, 'A family can develop only with a loving woman as its center.', 68443, 0), (452194, 'I''m thankful to God for having a family that''s been there for me. He''s been there from the time I was a child to even now with my family helping with my little boy. It''s worth more than words could ever describe. That''s one of the ways I''ve been able to stay grounded is thanks to family and God.', 72275, 0), (452195, 'Since 2005, I have not spent much time with my family. In fact I have spent more time at the Taj Landsend in Mumbai. It was my 100th visit recently, which means I have spent more than 400 days in that hotel, and that is a lot more than I have spent with my family.', 69702, 0), (452196, 'I read for the ''ah-ha''s,'' the information that makes a light bulb go off in my 