orgiving when it comes to other people''s families. The only family that ever horrifies you is your own.', 1002, 0), (452319, 'First and foremost comes my family and my life with Brad. We have so much joy in raising our children and teaching them about the world that nothing really compares to that.', 1380, 0), (452320, 'Getting married and starting a family has been a lifelong goal and one that I have persevered through different paths up to it!', 21687, 0), (452321, 'The last thing family and friends want is for you to spend money on them that you don''t have or that you can''t really spare.', 10090, 0), (452322, 'You don''t have to give birth to someone to have a family.', 68422, 0), (452323, 'Also, my mom and family are very important to me and I know that this is not expected.', 67850, 0), (452324, 'I love children and I get along with them great. It''s just that I believe if you''re going to be a parent, there has to be something inside you that says, ''I want a family.'' I don''t feel that sense of urgency.', 7961, 0), (452325, 'If you see a black family, it''s looting, but if it''s a white family they are looking for food.', 3290, 0), (452326, 'We will invest in our people, quality education, job opportunity, family, neighborhood, and yes, a thing we call America.', 17186, 0), (452327, 'We went to church every Sunday. When I was a kid, the only time I sang was around my family.', 69332, 0), (452328, 'First of all there is always that artistic challenge of creating something. Or the particular experience to take slum life in that period and make something out of it in the form of a book. And then I felt some kind of responsibility to my family.', 20529, 0), (452329, 'There''s nothing like a family crisis, especially a divorce, to force a person to re-evaluate his life.', 23151, 0), (452330, 'I''m not sure why no one wants to admit there''s a viable audience out there that believes in God and wants to see a movie with their family. The demand is there. The supply is not.', 1776, 0), (452331, 'I had a number of very strong personalities in my family. My father was a concert flutist, the solo flute for Toscanini.', 28610, 0), (452332, 'I grew up in a big family with a lot of kids around, and I definitely want to have children as well.', 69264, 0), (452333, 'A rescue mission doesn''t involve going in and just taking a child and leaving. You can''t just choose any child at random. Every kid has a case that is based on that child''s original family. So, we made it over to a village, found the child; we were interacting with the child.', 397, 0), (452334, 'You can say I had a severe case of ''Roots'' envy. I wanted to be like Alex Haley, and I wanted to be able to... do my family tree back to the slave ship and then reverse the Middle Passage, as I like to put it, and find the tribe or ethnic group that I was from in Africa.', 66934, 0), (452335, 'I am the baby in the family, and I always will be. I am actually very happy to have that position. But I still get teased. I don''t mind that.', 47095, 0), (452336, 'At my core, what I think we need to do is to get the basics right again. We need to rebuild our family structure, stay away from redefining marriage, and stand by marriage as a union between a man and a woman.', 72308, 0), (452337, 'It takes a lot of work to put together a marriage, to put together a family and a home.', 18433, 0), (452338, 'No one in my family was a reader of literary fiction. So, I didn''t have encouragement, but I didn''t have discouragement, because I don''t think anybody knew what that meant.', 1039, 0), (452339, 'My family kinda hit the skids. We were experiencing poverty at that point. We all got a job, where the whole family had to work as security guards and janitors. And I just got angry.', 14367, 0), (452340, 'Tennis just a game, family is forever.', 70497, 0), (452341, 'I have a great family, I live an amazing life.', 69354, 0), (452342, 'As a general thing, when a woman wears the pants in a 