 wonderful family growing up.', 72314, 0), (452425, 'I think as a child you know when it''s time for your parents to split. You realise they love each other, but they''re not in love with each other. And I think as a child it''s much better for your parents to split than for them to stay and have dysfunction within the family.', 67425, 0), (452426, 'My schedule can be hectic, so I''m always trying to find time to see my friends and family.', 71092, 0), (452427, 'My family said that I wanted to act even when I was a child living on a tea plantation in the jungle in India.', 71967, 0), (452428, 'I look to my family for my support. I''m fortunate to have a big family.', 72315, 0), (452429, 'I dabbled a little bit in acting in high school, and then I forgot about it completely. And then at about 25 I went to a class. I don''t think anybody in my family thought it was an intelligent choice. I don''t think anybody thought I''d succeed, which is understandable. I think they were just happy that I was doing something.', 72316, 0), (452430, 'You have to be funny about it and honest about it. You can''t leave yourself out of that mix. You have to be honest enough to say, I''m that messed-up one in the family.', 72317, 0), (452431, 'The Church is everywhere represented as one. It is one body, one family, one fold, one kingdom. It is one because pervaded by one Spirit. We are all baptized into one Spirit so as to become, says the apostle, on body.', 51004, 0), (452432, 'I have these visions of myself being thirty, thirty-five, forty having a family.', 72318, 0), (452433, 'That''s always at the heart and soul of Disney''s features, the feeling of a family values.', 72319, 0), (452434, 'Once you understand this way, you will be able to make your room alive; you will be able to design a house together with your family; a garden for your children; places where you can work; beautiful terraces where you can sit and dream.', 72320, 0), (452435, 'And whether it is equal pay, health care, Social Security, or family leave, this Congress has refused to address issues critical to hard-working American women.', 72267, 0), (452436, 'I don''t think anyone has a normal family.', 72321, 0), (452437, 'I doubt I''ll ever do another book collaboration; I''ve been spoiled. Roger and I both happened to move to New Mexico at about the same time, when we each had a family of young kids to raise. Socializing seemed to lead naturally to working together.', 48491, 0), (452438, 'Happy is said to be the family which can eat onions together. They are, for the time being, separate, from the world, and have a harmony of aspiration.', 48445, 0), (452439, 'The joke in our family is that we can cry reading the phone book.', 72322, 0), (452440, 'You have to defend your honor. And your family.', 66827, 0), (452441, 'When I''m ready, I plan to adopt. I still believe in family.', 65017, 0), (452442, 'I think everybody had difficulties with that dynamic, turning the family into a band and being constantly together. So everybody, as individuals. had things to sort out.', 72247, 0), (452443, 'And when I retired, trust me, not only did Nolan Ryan, but the entire Ryan family had withdrawals from baseball. And it was tough.', 69692, 0), (452444, 'Like all my family and class, I considered it a sign of weakness to show affection; to have been caught kissing my mother would have been a disgrace, and to have shown affection for my father would have been a disaster.', 71205, 0), (452445, 'Family, work, familiarity. Listen, if I had a magic wand and I could make myself really be happy, I''d zap me onto a farm. And I know nothing about farming.', 72323, 0), (452446, 'I grew up in a family in which political issues were often discussed, and debated intensely.', 72324, 0), (452447, 'I stay in tune with my family and God.', 34707, 0), (452448, 'That''s not the part of the story that I''m interested in, anyway. The part that I''m interested in is all the personal stuff. I tried to base the powers on family archetypes.', 30042, 0), (452449, 'Make a Goal Box, a chart of positive daily contact with a family when you are working with them.', 4139, 0), (452450, 'The most difficult is the first family, to bring someone out of the world.', 4139, 0);
